.TH "drm_open" 9 "drm_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_open \- open method for DRM file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_open
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct file *filp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
device inode
.IP "filp" 12
file pointer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must be used by drivers as their \fIfile_operations.open\fP method.
It looks up the correct DRM device and instantiates all the per-file
resources for it. It also calls the \fIdrm_driver.open\fP driver callback.

0 on success or negative errno value on falure.
.SH "RETURN"
